cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with object localization tasks. The use of Class Activation Maps (CAM) and Spatial Pyramid Averaged Max (SPAM) pooling also suggests that it may fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the mention of real-time performance and fast-backprojection technique may indicate that it could also be classified under Multimedia (cs.MM) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) categories.
